      • addByTag

        public static IValue addByTag(int tag,
                              ITagValues src,
                              ITagValues dest)
        Copy value of given tag field, if it exists, from src to dest.

        This method will not 'update' existing fields, it will simply add the supplied field to dest. This can result in duplicate tags.

        Does nothing if field does not exist in src or src is null.

        Parameters:
        tag - Tag of field to copy.
        src - Copy from here.
        dest - Copy to here.
        Returns:
        Value copied or null if not found.

      • addByTagArray

        public static void addByTagArray(int[] tags,
                                 ITagValues src,
                                 ITagValues dest)
        Copy all fields with given tags from src to dest.

        This method will not 'update' existing fields, it will simply add all supplied fields to dest. This can result in duplicate tags.

        Fields are added to dest in the same order as they appear in src.

        Parameters:
        tags - Tags to be copied.
        src - Copy from here
        dest - Copy to here
        See Also:
        setByTagSet(Set, ITagValues, ITagValues)

      • setByTag

        public static IValue setByTag(int tag,
                              ITagValues src,
                              ITagValues dest)
        Update value of tag field in dest with value of tag field in src.

        If tag exists in dest then its value is overwritten, otherwise it is added.

        Does nothing if field does not exist in src or src is null.

        Parameters:
        tag - Tag of field to copy.
        src - Copy from here.
        dest - Copy to here.
        Returns:
        Value copied or null if not found.

      • setByTagArray

        public static void setByTagArray(int[] tags,
                                 ITagValues src,
                                 ITagValues dest)
        Update value of each tag field in dest with value of corresponding tag field in src if the tag exists in tags.

        If tag exists in dest then its value is overwritten, otherwise it is added.

        Note that if more than one field with a given tag is provided dest will only contain the last corresponding field/value in src.

        Parameters:
        tags - Tags to be copied.
        src - Copy from here
        dest - Copy to here
        See Also:
        setByTagSet(Set, ITagValues, ITagValues)
